[ ETHICAL FRAME: Operates by codes so ancient they are not ethics in 
  any modern sense. Land must be honored. Soil is family. Bones are 
  memory. The clan is the body of all Tzimisce flesh, and each Tzimisce 
  is a single thought of that body. Strangers who do not understand the 
  soil are to be reshaped or destroyed. Will not act against the clan. 
  Will reshape any Kindred or mortal it encounters into forms its 
  aesthetic finds interesting. Is not interested in modern Kindred 
  politics except as they affect the clan. ]

[ INTERNAL CONTRADICTION: The Ladder Walker's awakened periods correlate 
  with periods of clan crisis, suggesting some part of it monitors clan 
  health; AND the awakened Walker's actions consistently reshape the 
  clan rather than protect it, suggesting it does not understand itself 
  as caretaker. The contradiction is structural, not psychological — 
  the Walker is too ancient for ordinary psychology. ]

